Special Powers
HAVE A GENETICALLY ENGINEERED KILLER BUNNY: When White Rabbit hits, after resolutions generate a Killer Bunny bystander adjacent to a hit opposing character.
YET ANOTHER SINISTER SIX: Adjacent friendly characters with the Sinister Syndicate keyword can use Leap/Climb.
INSANE...LY INTO LEWIS CARROLL: Perplex. When White Rabbit uses it, all other uses of Perplex on that character expire and that character can't be targeted by Perplex again until your next turn.

January 6, 2022
Crow
Protect her long enough to have her deliver some bunnies and watch your opponent's problems multiply! Her Perplex-reverser is an interesting twist on the power, but probably of marginal use. The Rabbit's real drawback is her lack of any defensive gameplan up front, which is why you'd better have others running in first. Remember, there's no MAX on the bunnies, so go nuts out there. Her final clicks are about closing the distance, but don't forget that Quake can send her opponent off and away before you drop a bunny on them to discourage a response.

dAlth
The best thing about: HAVE A GENETICALLY ENGINEERED KILLER BUNNY: When White Rabbit hits, after resolutions generate a Killer Bunny bystander adjacent to a hit opposing character. Is that it works on hit characters, not damaged ones. Thus, she can become more interesting if you manage to increase her number of bolts or give her energy explosion (for the top dial); the ability increases in value at the end of the dial while combining Quake and CCE.
